text: Danielle Hennig (born December 23, 1990 in Kelowna, British Columbia) is a female field hockey player, who played for the Canada national field hockey team as a defender at the 2011 Pan American Games,Canada at the 2011 Pan American Games#Field hockey 2013 Women's Pan American Cup, and 2014 Commonwealth Games, and the 2015 Pan American Games. ==References== Category:1990 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian female field hockey players Category:Field hockey people from British Columbia Category:Field hockey players at the 2011 Pan American Games Category:Field hockey players at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:Sportspeople from Kelowna Category:Pan American Games bronze medalists for Canada Category:Pan American Games medalists in field hockey Category:Pan American Games silver medalists for Canada Category:Field hockey players at the 2019 Pan American Games
